Class CourseDBStructure

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.fgonzalesv.assignment4.CourseDBStructure
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.fgonzalesv.assignment4.CourseDBStructureInterface

    public class CourseDBStructure
extends java.lang.Object
implements com.fgonzalesv.assignment4.CourseDBStructureInterface
    It is the data structure class that is used with the Course Database Manager class. This is a hash table with buckets implemented with an array of linked lists of CourseDBElements.
    Author:
    Fernando Gonzales-Vigil

      • add

        public void add(CourseDBElement element)
        The add method will take a CourseDBElement and add it to the data structure. If a linked list at the relevant hash code doesn’t exist, create a LinkedList with the first element being the CDE and add it to the HashTable. If the LinkedList already exists, add the CDE to the existing list
        Specified by:
        add in interface com.fgonzalesv.assignment4.CourseDBStructureInterface
        Parameters:
        element - - the CDE element

      • get

        public CourseDBElement get(int crn)
                    throws java.io.IOException
        The get method will take a CRN number and retrieve the CDE element of the data structure. If the element is not in the data structure, it returns an Exception.
